{
  "stem": "1062.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "When I was there, most of the people were not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "But behind the big camp, there was a little camp where the hospital was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "It was called the kleine lager or the totenlager, the small camp or the death camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "In there, where most of the Jews were kept.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "So they didn't put me in the-- in the death lager, in the death camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "I was in the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And they put me to work in Buchenwald in the quarry, which is called a Steinbruch, the Steinbruch.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "The Steinbruch was a penal for people-- it was like a penal, penal colony.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "Very few people survived the Steinbruch, because what happened over there, they-- they took a big rock and they put it on you.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And you had to carry it up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "And when you weren't up, so somebody, an SS man, would push you.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And then the rock would roll down and you [INAUDIBLE] fall down.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "The other guy would-- But when I was there, I met-- there was a guy who was a German civilian there who worked there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "And he left me a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "And I worked in the Steinbruch not much, maybe about three, four days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And from there I was taken to work on the highway near Weimar, on the main Autobahn by Weimar, passing through Weimar.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And when we went out, we went out at night, in the dark, because those days, I want you to know, this was already February, 1945, nothing in Germany moved during the day, the trains, the cars, even a horse.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "Because the planes, the American planes, the British planes, were always overhead and they would shoot up anything, everything.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
